---
import DefaultLayout from '@/layouts/DefaultLayout.astro';
import { LENDCITY } from '@/lib/lendcity';

const lastUpdated = 'April 28, 2026';
const phoneHref = `tel:${LENDCITY.phone.replace(/\D/g, '')}`;
---

<DefaultLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — FirstHomeGuide.ca"
  description="How FirstHomeGuide.ca collects, uses, and protects your personal information. Written for Canadian users under PIPEDA."
>
  <section class="section-padding container max-w-3xl">
    <p class="text-muted-foreground text-sm">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xxl leading-tight tracking-tight md:text-5xl">
      Privacy Policy
    </h1>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-4 leading-relaxed">
      This Privacy Policy explains how FirstHomeGuide.ca (&ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;us&rdquo;)
      collects, uses, and protects your personal information. It is written with reference
      to Canada&rsquo;s <em>Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act</em>
      (PIPEDA) and applicable provincial privacy legislation.
    </p>

    <div class="prose-legal mt-10 space-y-8 text-sm leading-relaxed md:text-base">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">1. Who we are</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          FirstHomeGuide.ca is a free educational website operated by LendCity (FSRA
          Brokerage Licence #12728) under Mortgage Architects. You can reach us through{' '}
          <a href="/contact" class="underline underline-offset-4">our contact page</a>,
          by phone at <a href={phoneHref} class="underline underline-offset-4">{LENDCITY.phone}</a>,
          or by mail at {LENDCITY.streetAddress}, {LENDCITY.city}, {LENDCITY.province}, {LENDCITY.postalCode}.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">2. Information we collect</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">We collect only the information needed to operate the site and respond to your requests:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>
            <strong>Information you give us voluntarily.</strong> Your name, email address, and
            any message contents when you use a contact form, book a call, share an article
            with a friend, or request information.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Booking information.</strong> When you book a call through our Nylas-powered
            scheduler, we collect your email, selected time, and any notes you provide.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Tool inputs.</strong> Our calculators (mortgage, affordability, closing cost,
            etc.) run entirely in your browser. The numbers you enter are not transmitted to us
            or stored on our servers unless you explicitly choose to share or email results.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Automatic technical data.</strong> Standard server logs (IP address, browser
            type, pages visited, referrer), cookies used for theme preference and service-worker
            caching, and aggregated analytics data.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">3. How we use your information</h2>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>To respond to your questions and deliver any information you request.</li>
          <li>To confirm, reschedule, or cancel calls you book with our team.</li>
          <li>To send transactional emails you initiate (e.g., sharing an article by email).</li>
          <li>To improve the site, diagnose errors, and prevent abuse.</li>
          <li>To comply with legal and regulatory obligations.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We do <strong>not</strong> sell your personal information. We do not use your
          information for unrelated marketing without your consent.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">4. Service providers</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">We rely on a small number of trusted processors to operate the site:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li><strong>Vercel</strong> — web hosting and edge delivery.</li>
          <li><strong>Elastic Email</strong> — sending transactional email (booking confirmations, article shares).</li>
          <li><strong>Nylas</strong> — calendar availability and booking infrastructure.</li>
          <li><strong>Upstash</strong> — rate-limit and cache storage for booking availability.</li>
          <li><strong>Supabase</strong> — database infrastructure (if you create an account or save progress in future features).</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Each provider receives only the information needed to perform its function and is
          contractually obligated to safeguard it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">5. Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We use strictly necessary cookies for site functionality (e.g., remembering your
          theme preference, service-worker caching) and may use privacy-respecting analytics
          cookies to measure aggregate site usage. You can disable cookies in your browser
          settings at any time; some features may stop working as a result.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">6. Your privacy rights</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Under PIPEDA and applicable provincial laws, you have the right to access, correct,
          or delete personal information we hold about you, and to withdraw consent to further
          processing. To make a request, email us through the{' '}
          <a href="/contact" class="underline underline-offset-4">contact page</a>. We will
          respond within 30 days.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">7. Data retention</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We retain booking and email records for the period required to provide the service
          and to meet tax, accounting, and legal obligations — typically no longer than seven
          years. Server logs are typically retained for 30&ndash;90 days.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">8. Security</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We use TLS encryption in transit, restricted access controls, and reputable cloud
          providers. No online system can be made perfectly secure. If we become aware of a
          privacy breach affecting you, we will notify you and the Office of the Privacy
          Commissioner of Canada in accordance with PIPEDA.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">9. Children</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          FirstHomeGuide.ca is intended for adults considering buying a home. We do not
          knowingly collect personal information from children under 18.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">10. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo;
          date at the top of the page reflects the most recent change. Material changes will
          be highlighted on the site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">11. Contact us</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Questions or concerns about privacy? Use our{' '}
          <a href="/contact" class="underline underline-offset-4">contact page</a>, call{' '}
          <a href={phoneHref} class="underline underline-offset-4">{LENDCITY.phone}</a>,
          or write to LendCity at:
        </p>
        <address class="mt-3 not-italic">
          LendCity<br />
          {LENDCITY.streetAddress}<br />
          {LENDCITY.city}, {LENDCITY.province}, {LENDCITY.postalCode}<br />
          {LENDCITY.country}
        </address>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</DefaultLayout>
